vs/alsc/awardsgrants/bookmedia/belpremedal/belprepast/index.cfm The Pura Belpr\u00e9 Winners], Accessed April 7, 2009</ref> the [[International Reading Association|International Reading Association (IRA)]],<ref>[http://www.reading.org/Resources/AwardsandGrants/childrens_ira.aspx IRA Children's and Young Adult's Book Awards] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130804195444/http://www.reading.org/Resources/AwardsandGrants/childrens_ira.aspx |date=2013-08-04 }}, Accessed April 7, 2009</ref> and the [[New York Public Library]].<ref>[http://www.ezra-jack-keats.org/bookawards/index.html The Ezra Jack Keats and New York Public Library New Writer and New Illustrator Award for Children's Books] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080622003816/http://www.ezra-jack-keats.org/bookawards/index.html |date=2008-06-22 }}, Accessed April 7, 2009</ref>\n\n'''Major awards won by Lee & Low Books'''\n{|class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n!Award\n!Citation\n!Year\n!Creator\n!Book\n|-  style=\"background:LemonChiffon; color:black\"\n| [[Coretta Scott King Award|Coretta Scott King Author Honor Award]]\n| Winner\n| 2011\n| {{sort|G. Neri}}\n| [[Yummy: the Last Days of a Southside Shorty]]\n|-  style=\"background:LemonChiffon; color:black\"\n| [[Coretta Scott King Award|Coretta Scott King Author Award]]\n| Winner\n| 1974\n| {{sort|Mathis,Sharon Bell|Sharon Bell Mathis}}\n| ''Ray Charles''\n|-\n| [[Coretta Scott King Award|Coretta Scott King Author Award]]\n| Honor\n| 1976\n| {{sort|Greenfield,Eloise|[[Eloise Greenfield]]}}\n| ''Paul Robeson''\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon; color:black\"\n| [[Coretta Scott King Award|Coretta Scott King Illustrator Award]]\n| Winner\n| 1998\n| {{sort|Steptoe,Javaka|Javaka Steptoe}}\n| ''In Daddy's Arms I Am Tall: African Americans Celebrating Fathers''\n|- style=\"background:LemonChiffon; color:black\"\n| [[Coretta Scott King Award|Coretta Scott King Illustrator Award]]\n| Winner\n| 1974\n| {{sort|Ford,George|George Ford (illustrator)|Geo